<Layout title="About - Learn Ultrasound Focusing" description="About the Learn Ultrasound Focusing project and its educational goals">
  <div class="about-container">
    <div class="page-header">
      <h1>üìñ About This Project</h1>
      <p>Learn about the educational goals, development process, and background of the Learn Ultrasound Focusing project.</p>
    </div>

    <section class="about-section">
      <h2>Project Overview</h2>
      <div class="content-card">
        <p>
          Learn Ultrasound Focusing is an interactive educational platform designed to help students, researchers, and professionals understand the principles of ultrasound array focusing and beamforming. Through hands-on visualizations and comprehensive theoretical resources, this project bridges the gap between abstract mathematical concepts and practical ultrasound applications.
        </p>
        <p>
          The project combines real-time interactive simulations with detailed theoretical explanations, allowing learners to experiment with different parameters and immediately see the effects on ultrasound beam patterns and focusing behavior.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="about-section">
      <h2>Educational Goals</h2>
      <div class="goals-grid">
        <div class="goal-card">
          <div class="goal-icon">üéØ</div>
          <h3>Conceptual Understanding</h3>
          <p>Help learners develop intuitive understanding of how ultrasound arrays focus acoustic energy through precise timing control and wave interference.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="goal-card">
          <div class="goal-icon">‚ö°</div>
          <h3>Interactive Learning</h3>
          <p>Provide hands-on experience with parameter adjustment and real-time visualization to reinforce theoretical concepts through experimentation.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="goal-card">
          <div class="goal-icon">üî¨</div>
          <h3>Research Applications</h3>
          <p>Bridge academic theory with practical applications in medical imaging, therapeutic ultrasound, and non-destructive testing.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="goal-card">
          <div class="goal-icon">üåê</div>
          <h3>Accessible Education</h3>
          <p>Make advanced ultrasound concepts accessible to a broad audience through clear explanations and interactive demonstrations.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="about-section">
      <h2>Target Audience</h2>
      <div class="audience-grid">
        <div class="audience-card">
          <h3>üéì Students</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Biomedical engineering undergraduates and graduates</li>
            <li>Physics students studying wave mechanics</li>
            <li>Medical physics students</li>
            <li>Electrical engineering students in signal processing</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="audience-card">
          <h3>üî¨ Researchers</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Ultrasound system developers</li>
            <li>Medical imaging researchers</li>
            <li>Acoustic engineers</li>
            <li>Scientists working with phased arrays</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="audience-card">
          <h3>üë©‚Äç‚öïÔ∏è Professionals</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Medical physicists and technologists</li>
            <li>Ultrasound equipment operators</li>
            <li>Clinical engineers</li>
            <li>Industry professionals in ultrasound</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="about-section">
      <h2>Key Features</h2>
      <div class="features-list">
        <div class="feature-item">
          <div class="feature-header">
            <div class="feature-icon">üéÆ</div>
            <h3>Real-time Interactive Visualization</h3>
          </div>
          <p>Adjust array parameters, target positions, and timing controls to see immediate effects on ultrasound beam patterns and wave propagation.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="feature-item">
          <div class="feature-header">
            <div class="feature-icon">üìä</div>
            <h3>Parameter Exploration</h3>
          </div>
          <p>Experiment with number of elements, element spacing, focusing targets, and wave speeds to understand their impact on beam characteristics.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="feature-item">
          <div class="feature-header">
            <div class="feature-icon">üé¨</div>
            <h3>Animation and Recording</h3>
          </div>
          <p>Generate frame-by-frame animations of wave propagation and download movies for presentations or further analysis.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="feature-item">
          <div class="feature-header">
            <div class="feature-icon">üìö</div>
            <h3>Comprehensive Theory</h3>
          </div>
          <p>Access detailed explanations of the mathematical and physical principles underlying ultrasound focusing and beamforming.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="about-section">
      <h2>Development Background</h2>
      <div class="content-card">
        <p>
          This project emerged from the need for better educational tools in ultrasound physics and engineering. Traditional textbook explanations, while mathematically rigorous, often fail to provide the intuitive understanding that comes from seeing wave interactions in action.
        </p>
        <p>
          The interactive visualization approach allows learners to develop both mathematical understanding and physical intuition simultaneously. By manipulating parameters and observing results in real-time, users can explore "what-if" scenarios that would be difficult or impossible to demonstrate in traditional classroom settings.
        </p>
        <p>
          The project is built using modern web technologies to ensure accessibility across different devices and platforms, making it available to anyone with a web browser.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="about-section">
      <h2>Contributing and Feedback</h2>
      <div class="content-card">
        <p>
          This is an open-source educational project, and we welcome contributions from the community. Whether you're interested in:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Content development:</strong> Adding new visualizations or theoretical explanations</li>
          <li><strong>Technical improvements:</strong> Enhancing the user interface or simulation accuracy</li>
          <li><strong>Educational feedback:</strong> Suggesting improvements to explanations or examples</li>
          <li><strong>Bug reports:</strong> Identifying and helping fix issues</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          Your input helps make this resource better for the entire ultrasound education community. Visit our GitHub repository to get involved or provide feedback.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="about-section">
      <h2>Acknowledgments</h2>
      <div class="content-card">
        <p>
          This project builds upon decades of research in ultrasound physics, array signal processing, and educational technology. We acknowledge the contributions of researchers and educators who have developed the theoretical foundations and practical applications that make modern ultrasound systems possible.
        </p>
        <p>
          Special thanks to the open-source community for providing the tools and frameworks that enable projects like this to exist and be freely accessible to learners worldwide.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>
  </div>
</Layout>

<style>
  .about-container {
    max-width: 900px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .page-header {
    text-align: center;
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
    padding: 2rem;
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, #f8fafc 0%, #e2e8f0 100%);
    border-radius: 12px;
  }

  .page-header h1 {
    font-size: 2.5rem;
    margin: 0 0 1rem 0;
    color: #1e293b;
  }

  .page-header p {
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    color: #64748b;
    margin: 0;
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  .about-section {
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
  }

  .about-section h2 {
    font-size: 2rem;
    color: #1e293b;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
    padding-bottom: 0.5rem;
    border-bottom: 3px solid #06b6d4;
  }

  .content-card {
    background: white;
    padding: 2rem;
    border-radius: 12px;
    box-shadow: 0 4px 6px rgba(0,0,0,0.05);
    border: 1px solid #e2e8f0;
  }

  .content-card p {
    color: #64748b;
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  .content-card p:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .content-card ul {
    color: #64748b;
    line-height: 1.7;
    padding-left: 1.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  .content-card li {
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .goals-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(250px, 1fr));
    gap: 1.5rem;
  }

  .goal-card {
    background: white;
    padding: 2rem;
    border-radius: 12px;
    box-shadow: 0 4px 6px rgba(0,0,0,0.05);
    border: 1px solid #e2e8f0;
    text-align: center;
    transition: transform 0.3s ease;
  }

  .goal-card:hover {
    transform: translateY(-4px);
  }

  .goal-icon {
    font-size: 3rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .goal-card h3 {
    color: #1e293b;
    margin: 0 0 1rem 0;
    font-size: 1.25rem;
  }

  .goal-card p {
    color: #64748b;
    line-height: 1.6;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .audience-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(280px, 1fr));
    gap: 1.5rem;
  }

  .audience-card {
    background: white;
    padding: 2rem;
    border-radius: 12px;
    box-shadow: 0 4px 6px rgba(0,0,0,0.05);
    border: 1px solid #e2e8f0;
  }

  .audience-card h3 {
    color: #1e293b;
    margin: 0 0 1rem 0;
    font-size: 1.25rem;
  }

  .audience-card ul {
    color: #64748b;
    line-height: 1.6;
    padding-left: 1.5rem;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .audience-card li {
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .features-list {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1.5rem;
  }

  .feature-item {
    background: white;
    padding: 2rem;
    border-radius: 12px;
    box-shadow: 0 4px 6px rgba(0,0,0,0.05);
    border: 1px solid #e2e8f0;
  }

  .feature-header {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 1rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .feature-header .feature-icon {
    font-size: 2rem;
  }

  .feature-header h3 {
    color: #1e293b;
    margin: 0;
    font-size: 1.25rem;
  }

  .feature-item p {
    color: #64748b;
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin: 0;
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .about-container {
      padding: 0 1rem;
    }

    .page-header {
      padding: 1.5rem;
    }

    .page-header h1 {
      font-size: 2rem;
    }

    .page-header p {
      font-size: 1rem;
    }

    .about-section h2 {
      font-size: 1.75rem;
    }

    .content-card,
    .goal-card,
    .audience-card,
    .feature-item {
      padding: 1.5rem;
    }

    .goals-grid,
    .audience-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }

    .feature-header {
      flex-direction: column;
      text-align: center;
      gap: 0.5rem;
    }
  }
</style>
